r cravings, reducing stress, and ultimately living a fuller life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aBehavior modification. 0aChange (Psychology). 0aCompulsive behavior. 0aHabit breaking. 0aHabit. 7aBODY, MIND & SPIRIT / Mindfulness & Meditation.2bisacsh1 aKabat-Zinn, Jon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKabat-Zinn, Jon.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311063898140uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030022760440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300227604423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300227604/original  a978-3-11-063898-1  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles